Reasoning: The paper describes NMT systems for English-Czech news translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of the Transformer model, which is a popular deep learning architecture for NLP tasks and falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of the Marian framework, which is a neural machine translation toolkit, and the semi-automatic analysis of lexical coherence, which could fall under the categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV) for text analysis.
